net.sf.JRecord.IO

Class AbstractLineReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.JRecord.IO.AbstractLineReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IReadLine
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BasicTextLineReader, ContinuousLineReader, LineByteRecordReaderWrapper, XmlLineReader, ZOldBinary4680LineReader

    public abstract class AbstractLineReader
extends java.lang.Object
implements IReadLine
    This abstract class is the base class for all Line~Reader classes. A LineReader reads a file as a series of AbstractLines. 
    Example:
 
      AbstractLineReader reader = JRecordInterface1.COBOL
              .newIOBuilder("file-name")
                  .setFileOrganization(Constants.IO_FIXED_LENGTH)
                  .setDialect(ICopybookDialects.FMT_FUJITSU)
              .newReader("Data-Filename");
              
      while ((l = reader.read()) != null) { ... }
      reader.closer()
    Author:
    Bruce Martin
